Ok, so this is tough for me. I have fought myself over whether to write this review because it's my favorite breakfast spot and it's usually packed in waves in the morning. I don't want my wait to be longer, since I'm normally running late lol.  Here goes.... This place looks like a little dive corner bakery. Nothing special, but always a curiously long line in the morning. They make, in my opinion, the best coffee in the neighborhood. You won't find fancy lattes or pumkin spice anything here, but simply the best Colombian coffee with the traditional boiled milk. WARNING: it's not for the weak of heart! It doesn't taste as strong as it is, which is nice for me, but it will race your heart if you aren't used to strong, espresso-like coffee. The breads 😍😍😍😍😍 a variety of traditional Colombian breads, also, the best in the area. I recommend the pan de bono, cambray, or rosca. They also have empanadas cheese filled sweet plantains, sausages and arepas of cheese or sweet corn. ALL. DELICIOUS. The prices are sooo good you could buy one of everything I mentioned and barely reach $20 They also serve lunches of rice and beans and different meats... never had them but I'm sure they are yummy. I'm more of a breakfast lady myself. In a nutshell, this is the gem of Sunset Park.
